inn1.comm: Praveen Kumar starts by landing the ball on a good length outside off, Gilchrist defends back down
strays on to the legs this time and Gilchrist doesn't miss it, tucking it off the legs and they come back for three as the ball races in front of midwicket on a fast outfield
pushes the ball down off on a good length, Hayden lets the ball go through on the back foot first up
overpitched on off and Hayden drives forward hard on the front foot back past the bowler through mid-off, treated that ball with some disdain
a touch short this time outside off, and Hayden opens the face to run it down off the back foot to third man
oh, a false shot from Hayden, looking to boost it through midwicket from way outside off and has swivelled through the shot way before the ball has got to him
across the left hander, hits a nagging length immediately and just outside off, the batsman shoulders arms
across the left hander again, who shoulders arms again as the ball kicks through on a good length, a wide enough angle for him to leave
a sharp delivery at 142.5kph, carries on well through to Dhoni as the ball pitches wide outside off and moves on wider, again Hayden leaves
booms it wide again down the channel, just a touch too wide for the umpire's liking
but this ball's too much on the legs, the ball tickled off the pads and it races across the billiard-table surface to fine leg
pushed through on a good length and better line this time outside off
pushed down on a good length again, the batsman leaves
good one, straight, and forcing Gilchrist to defend down with a jump in line with middle and off
hey now, ahort and outside off and Gilchrist rocks back on and cuts hard through the covers, the ball goes all the way as he put all his muscle behind that one
a wide down leg-side this time, Gilchrist lets it go through
on off and middle, better ball this time, defended on the front foot now
short ball on off and Gilchrist goes for the hook, not quite getting over the ball as it came on to him faster than antichipated and he scoops up to Yuvraj at mid-on who takes the catch cat-cool
just outside off, continues to stay over for the left hander, on a good length and he defends on the back foot
shortish ball outside off, punched out to the covers
Ponting comes out to look to drive to the covers, but ends up adjusting to the good length and defending on the front foot
pushed on to the legs, pretty good length, pushed on the front foot out to short midwicket, more defensively than anything
back of a length outside off and Ponting pushes over wide of mid-on
rushed on to him, clipping the pad in line with middle, the ball had pitched outside leg
a touch too straight on leg and Hayden brushes it out in front of square and they take the second through some good running
good-length ball outside off, pushed out to mid-on
chased round outside off
Ponting goes! The batsman looked to pull a short one round from outside off, the ball not quite getting up, and the inside edge crashes hard on to the sticks
outside off, Clarke starts with a leave
pushed through on a good length outside off
defended on the back foot back to mid-off
shortish ball on middle, driven off the legs through midwicket and that's a tidy shot to get off the mark
turned off the legs behind square
short ball on off, defended down on the front foot and in comes the call of "Wait on, wait on"
short ball on off, rising up and played down off the back foot to gully, well negotiated
pushed back in to the right hander who defends back down

fabulous delivery from Ishant, taking the inside edge as Clarke goes to forward defend but is beaten by the inswing, the ball coming back in off the seam from outside off and the pace, and Dhoni takes the catch
lets the ball go through outside off on a good length
stays over the wicket and fires across the left hander on a good length who opts, probably wisely, to leave
good-length ball on off, Hayden defends into the covers
short ball on off, Hayden advances way down the track and fires hard and well over mdiwicket with a powerful swipe
a better ball, fuller on off, and the batsman fends down off the back foot into the gully
a good-length ball on middle and leg, forced off the front foot straight out to mid-on
great fielding from the reliable Uthappa with a dive to stop the ball as it was cut hard to backward point from a short one on off
tidy ball, defended on the front foot
Ishant fires in the bouncer, very well directed indeed, low as bouncers go, and forced over the shoulders as he ducks
good length on off, tucked into the legs, defensively
good line outside off, left alone
Hayden comes down to try to force the ball through midwicket, Ishant crashes it into the pads in line with leg
tucked off the legs down to long leg and it's well thrown back in
defended on the front foot in line with off
defended on the back foot in line with middle and off, well bowled, the ball nipping in from outside off
outside off, good length, defended back down off the back foot
good line and length and Symonds can only defend
on the legs, just back of a length, turned the slower ball away quite fine and with good wrists
short ball on off, defended off the back foot into the covers
forced up there in line with off, cut hard well to deep point
pushed up there well outside off, defended out to the covers
a touch too straight, overpitched on middle, and driven out hard off the legs through midwicket, using a touch of bottom hand to help him
a fraction short outside off, and wide, cut hard through point and the ball goes all the way, Symonds put everything he had behind that one and then only had to take two steps out of his crease
good length ball now, on middle and off, defended on the front foot with a push into short midwicket and Symonds follows up with a booming "No!"
outside off, short, and Symonds doesn't get hold of that one, a back-foot cut to point where a misfield allows the single
oh, Kumar found extra bounce there from one which pitches outside off and carried on a touch, Symonds playing under it with a would-be steer
outside off, good length, driven to the covers this time
stands tall and waits for what happens to be a good-length ball, driven into the covers
drives strongly on the front foot, but not with great timing, to the covers and in comes the "Waiting!" call
Symonds gets on the front foot, coming out to look to push through midwicket, he manages the drive but doesn't have the timing or the placement to force it on
excellent stop at point, Symonds cuts hard and sets off, thinking it's easily beaten the fielder whose dive cuts it off
gets some good swing first up, the ball carrying on to the legs, and Hayden flicks it off the pads to midwicket
oh, so close, Hayden was that far from inside-edging on as he waits for a good-length ball on off, and chops back just wide of the leg stump
a short ball wide a touch wide outside off, and the batsman launches into a hard straight drive, Irfan putting up his hand but doesn't quite get the fingertip
poor ball, short and outside off, and it got the treatment, Hayden muscles into a hard, flowing cut off the back foot, leaning hard into that one
swing into the left hander, driven out to the covers on the front foot
outside off, cut hard behind point
defended down off the back foot, a short ball this time
turned off the legs in front of square this time
driven out to the covers on the front foot
well run out to mid-on this time
on the legs, turned off in front of midwicket and there's a direct shy, but he looked to be just home
right up there on off, and stabbed down on the front foot down to third man
swing outside off, too full, and cut that slower ball hard off the back foot just behind point, the ball goes all the way
good-length delivery outside off, cut hard off the back foot to the cover ring
very well bowled indeed, a much slower ball deceived Hayden completely and forced him to push away outside off, inside the line, and there was nearly a stumping chance for Dhoni
a short ball again outside off, cut hard off the back foot and that flashes all the way, Hayden taking control out there
closer to the stumps this time but still wide, and cut hard once more
again he finds the gap with another crashing cut behind point, Hayden bringing up a hard-hitting fifty at the same time
a touch of room outside off, allows Symonds to drive hard to the diving cover
outside leg, clipped through point and they ease through the single
outside off, shortish, and cut hard to the covers
planted through on a good length across the left hander who elects to leave
slightly overpitched, and driven out to mid-on
outside off, jabbed into the covers this time
defended on the front foot
driven out to mid-off who gets a hand on it but he didn't fully stop it so they shuffle through
outside off, driven out wide of mid-on towards Ishant, the batsmen deciding not to try for the two
well bowled, Hayden didn't quite deal with that one properly, the ball swivelling off behind him
big loop, but overpitched and Hayden wins that mini-battle of a ball with a cover drive, hitting through the line and through the gap
pitches outside leg and whirs up on middle, Hayden turns it off the legs to midwicket
on the legs, brushed out to fine leg, Kumar
good delivery at 147.8kph, just across the left hander who presses it to mid-off
width outside off, cut into the covers off the back foot
a fuller delivery than he was expecting, is almost cut in two as he bends over to try to push to midwicket, the edge going down
width outside off and a full ball, he cuts into the ground out to point who takes it and pretends to throw it in celebration, though it was a bump ball
very wide outside off, cut out behind point towards the boundary
down leg, Symonds left it alone
short ball outside off and drives on the up with fast hands
good recovery ball, fired in on the dime, defended forward
wide down leg once more and the crowd cheers
that would have been another wide, but perhaps a deliberate one, goung for the stumping as he saw Symonds coming, the batsman kicks it defensively
down the legs this time, brushed on
outside leg, pressed down into the leg side this time
outside off, driven to the covers
straight and defended back down into the pitch
shortish ball outside off, pushed into midwicket this time
outside off, driven back towards the bowler
a full ball on off, defended on the front foot
on middle and leg, glanced hard through fine leg
on the legs, pushed off in front of square for an easy single
picks off the single off the back foot to mid-off
driven out on the front foot
defended on the front foot this time
outside off, cut into the covers this time
well bowled on off, Hayden waits and defends back down off the back foot
more loop, pitching on middle and off and turning out to off, Hayden lets it go through sensibly
turns it out past the batsman, pushed off the back foot into the covers and there's a misfield
defended on the front foot
driven out to mid-off this time
on middle and leg, tucked behind square for an easy single
well bowled on middle, pushed up there and defended forward
more of the same, a good, tidy over first up, the batsmen just taking a look at him
pushed out for a quick single
and another single brings Hayden back on strike
defended down off the back foot
outside off, cut into the ground and they run through once more
looped on to the legs, Symonds presses out in front of short midwicket and they look for the single and decide it's not there
outside off, a touch too full, gets away with it, worked out to mid-off
big loop up there crashing on to off, Hayden pushes out for a gentle single
on the legs now, brushed down to fine leg and they jog up the single
outside off, driven out hard to long-off where Tendulkar returns
outside off, Symonds played it late with a cut out to point, making room as the ball came back in at him
outside off, Hayden guides down easily off the back foot to short third man

overpitched in line with off and driven out to mid-on to bring up a very well worked hundred-run partnership which has changed the complexion of the game, rescuing their side from 3 for not very many. More work lies ahead, though, of course
outside off, some room, and Symonds drives up straight and hard aerially out to Kumar in the deep on the on-side, deep midwicket in fact
pushed past the left hander from over the wicket, left alone
tight delivery in line with middle, defended on the front foot
on the legs, swept down to the man there for that shot on the short 45
driven out to mid-on and they run through
cut gently down off the back foot to gully
outside off, pushed down back towards the bowler as the ball came into him
on the legs, and turned down gently behind square
pushed across him, left alone
an inside edge on to the shoe, Hussey looking to work to short midwicket, the ball popped up short of the bowler
turned back in to him from outside off, defended on the front foot
turned off the front foot in line with middle to midwicket
good loop in line with off, driven out to deep mid-off who throws back in without fuss
across the left hander and finds the edge but doesn't carry to first slip as he stabbbed forward in defence
pushed on to the back foot to defend
pushed right across the left hander who doesn't pick the bounce and is surprised by it, great rip past him
some testing loop this time, forced past him again
just a touch straight now, on middle, Hussey rocks back and creates room to force to midwicket on the front foot
pushed across the left hander who leaves it on its way past him, pitching outside and turning wider, on a full length
average fielding from Irfan who gets in position for the long barrier method, but leaves a yawning gap through which the ball hops like an inquisitive rabbit
defended forward this time
opens the face and guides it down to third man
pushed forward this time
a wide ball this time, down leg, Hussey goes to chase it round
driven out straight to long off and another poor piece of fielding, this time from (sshh) Tendulkar who leant down lazily with one hand and ended up knocking it further down the ground
driven out towards mid-off
cut to point and takes a bit of a bad bobble into the shoulder
Hayden gets down early to play the sweep to a full ball, and sends it just behind square for a good catch by Chawla who keeps his head and hangs on well
pushed forward this time
driven out wide of the covers
defended back down on the front foot in line with off
comes right forward to defend on the front foot
comes in from outside off, pushed forward to the covers
defended right down on to the back foot
defended forward on the front foot this time
outside off, pushed back to the bowler
outside off, pushed away from the right hander who defends back down into the turf
a sweep shot goes in the air but just safe
comes out to meet the ball on off and defends into the covers
on off, turned to midwicket with a roll of the wrists, and there's something of a misthrow from Raina
tossed in outside leg turned back in to the batsman who in turn turns it back out to midwicket
defended on the front foot, quietly
turned back in to the right hander who smooths it out to midwicket
up there on off, driven back out to the covers where Raina does the job
driven out easily to mid-on this time
turned in outside off, pushed over to midwicket this time for some gentle running
pushes too far down leg this time
some turn in back towards off, catches the outside edge as it rolls up the bat, but goes safe to the off side
driven out to mid-on this time
outside off, and Hopes nearly edges back on to his stumps, the ball goes down behind the keeper
a tight ball in line with middle, defended on the front foot
defended into the covers this time
defends on the front foot
more defence
driven out to mid-off on the front foot
clamps bat down on ball, pushing it to mid-on
outside off, a full delivery, driven out on to the legs, and it's picked up at mid-on
outside off, the batsman squeezes out to short midwicket
stands forward and defends on the front foot in line with middle
outside off, driven out on the full to short midwicket
on off, works across the spin, trying to brush it out to the legs
comes forward and defends on the front foot
a touch too short , straight, and pulled over in front of deep midwicket, kicked in inside the rope
pitched outside leg, comes back in and for some reason they appeal
on middle and off, turned out to midwicket
turned from outside off back into the right hander who drives out to teh covers
on to the legs, worked out in front of square this time
worked out in front of midwicket this time
a cute reverse sweep goes down to third man and the throw comes back in
pushed up there on the legs, defended tidily this time
outside off, turned to short midwicket
driven out to mid-on
driven out on the leg side once again, only a push really
defended this time, the bowler has done well this over
drags that one short and pulls hard to the rope
defended on the front foot
driven forward
goes for the forward drive but the edge splays wide to point
outside off, cut hard to point
slower ball, well bowled, defended into the covers
turned back into him from outside off and the batsman pulls hard in front of midwicket, just eluding the fielder
a touch short and on the legs, turned off the pads to short midwicket
defended on the front foot this time
driven out to long-off for an easy single
pushes him on to the back foot in line with leg, turned out to square
extra loop to that one which comes in outside off, and is driven out wide of long-off
short ball, pulled high and hard over midwicket
on the money, defended on off into short cover
slower ball worked across the right hander from over the wicket, the batsman cuts off the back foot towards third man
pushed across him, but a touch too wide
pushed past the outside edge, the batsman plays defensively inside the line
cut out to point this time
rolled across him outside off, defended into the covers
overpitched on off, driven out to long-off
turned back in on off, pushed forward on the front foot, defensively
waits outside off and pushes into the covers
outside off, cut off the back foot to the gully
offers some width outside off, Hopes shapes to cut to point, and nicks a fine edge on the top of the blade, Dhoni begins to roar before he's even taken the ball
curls it outside off and the batsman pushes tamely into the covers
into the legs, full ball, defended on the front foot
driven out to the covers slowly
drags it a touch wide and short, and guided out off the back foot to point
waits for the ball which rises a touch and forces it out to mid-off
picks it up on the toes in line with off and dig-drives it out to mid-off
a touch of width again, cut out to point
extra bounce on the legs, dealt with by a tuck down
worked out to the off-side this time
outside off, waits on the back foot to drive out to the covers
pushed into the legs, the batsman pushes back out to the leg-side
outside off this time, pitched up, and the batsman drives back out to mid-off
waits on the back foot outside off, and drives out straight
outside off, the ball keeps very low indeed, and the batsman plays nowhere near it, looking to hoick the ball from outside off through midwicket
turned off the legs behind square this time
outside off, a hint of room to drive back out in front of point
some spin from outside off back into the batsman who drives out off the back foot to the covers
spin from off back in to the batsman who helps it behind square
gives this one some extra loop on middle and leg, the batsman turns it out to midwicket and they run through easily
driven out to the covers
driven back out to the bowler
outside off, enough room to cut in front of point this time
pushed from outside off to the legs in front of midwicket for a half-stop of a dive which allows the single
pressed down off the back foot to short third man
reaches out and sweeps down behind him
pushed back out to square for a quick single
just outside off, driven out to long-on this time
comes out and defends on the front foot
width outside off, driven to the covers on the front foot and it's cut off
turned behind square for another easy single
cut off the back foot into the covers
just to say a touch short outside off, pushed down off the back foot into the covers and the batsmen run through quickly
outside off, pulled down just in front of square and again they run through
outside off, cut hard off the back foot into the ground and the fielder takes the ball
outside off, dragged to square across the line
short ball outside off, pulled to the fielder at midwicket
tries to york him, just a touch short for that, driven back out to long-on
oh, a bye down off, the ball keeping very low and crashes into Dhoni's pads who then chases, shies, and was so close to having Hogg miles out
pushed forward this time
cut to point now
another slower ball, outside off, cut into the covers
overpitches on off and Hussey swipes out towards Tendulkar at long-on
full ball on off, driven out to long-off
full ball outside off, well bowled, and chopped down into the off-side
outside off, driven out through the covers to the man in deep
tight ball on off, the batsman drops his hands down on the ball and they run through quickly

full toss goes straight and the batsman pulls round to deep square where Harbhajan slides into it, takes it on the bounce  and rifles in the throw to Dhoni who takes the stumps but the batsman is already back in
full toss on off and Hussey comes out to meet it and sweeps it round through fine leg
outside off, Hussey goes to pull it to midwicket, misses, the ball goes behind and they race through but Dhoni throws back to the bowler who throws on to the sticks
pushes it on to the legs, driven back out to the bowler who nearly throws down the non-striker's stumps and Lee is nearly run out off his first ball
comes round the wicket, fires in wide, and it's pushed out off the back foot to point
comes back in to the right hander who pushes back out to the covers
round the wicket again, comes in again, pushed out to point and they run through, Rohit aims at the non-striker's stumps and allows the overthrow
slower ball, driven up and over the bowler and they come back for two after something of a little mix-up
over the wicket, pushed off the legs wide of mid-on
over the wicket, across the right hander, the slower ball drops wide outside off, Lee goes for the flashing pull and connects only with air
the slower ball, Lee comes down the track, he's deceived and very nearly bowled as the ball goes on just past the sticks
backs away to leg, Irfan follows him and he pulls it round behind square
outside off, driven hard wide of midwicket and there's two fours in a row for Lee who's boosting his side late on
slower ball of a full toss and Lee drives hard through backward point for another four
Rohit takes the catch now as Lee drives very hard and high over to long-off, opening his shoulders but not quite getting the right trajectory
driven out to point for a quick single
swirls the ball full on to the legs, tucked out wide of mid-on for a quick single
pushed in on the legs and driven out off the inside edge to fine leg, well kept in by the fielder on the rope
outside off, stab-cuts into the ground, the batsman backing away
backs way away to leg and squeezes the ball out to leg at the last second
slower ball on off, Johnson drives out to the legs and they get back for a comfortable two

inn2.comm: runs immediately, with a defensive down into the gap at gully and some very hard running between the batsmen
off the mark straight away as well, tucking Lee off his hips and into the vacancy wide of square leg, and fine leg does the covering up

slides down leg stump, Uthappa looks to work it off the hips and wide is called, Gilchrist dives to his left and stops one-handed, then collects and has a throw at the stumps but Uthappa gets back in time
thats on the dime and Uthappa defends off the front foot
express delivery, 141ks and seaming away off a great length to get Uthappa pushing away from his body ... lucky not to get a tickle on that
back of a length and he gets right over it in hurried defence
positive stroke, pushed off the front foot and point moves quickly
top delivery, right on the money, with lift that beats Tendulkar as he pushes off the front foot ... that ball held its line and straightened
this time he makes sure to stretch well forward and defend
dangerous leave, as the slower one goes on straight
pitches outside leg and he turns it straight to midwicket
close! Reaches out to drive a full one and inside-edges to fine leg
133.6ks, on a length outside off and he leaves it be
too straight and Uthappa works it past square leg for one
ripper! 145ks, short and rising and gets Tendulkar sniffing leather
a tad too straight, tapped to midwicket for an urgent single
short on the stumps and he turns it straight to square leg
walks across the stumps, Lee bowls it down leg and wide is called
back of a length and he's up on the toes, pushing through point
shapes to work it across the line but defends to point instead
comes onto the front foot and squeezes a full one past cover-point
pushed across him off a short length and he shoulders arms
bang, thats four, as he slams the short and wide one over point
good comeback, on the stumps and its tightly defended
again, back of a length but Tendulkar is right behind the line
lets this one go as it hits a wider length and seams away
top shot, worked off the hips down to fine leg, running across
short one, sits up nicely and its pushed with soft  hands to point and Tendulkar responds well to Uthappa's call for the quick single
slower ball, just 114ksfree hit
full and fast, Uthappa drives hard but to Symonds at extra cover, who collects and fires in an accurate throw to the stumps
gets forward, then back, nearly beaten by the slower ball and he has to check the shot, the ball flies in the air wide of gully
its full, he shuffles across and flicks but cannot beat square leg
back of a length, he hops and runs it to third man for a single
short ball outside off, and Tendulkar cuts hard off the back foot... but straight to the fielder, Ponting at short point who snaps it up on the bounce and rocks back with the momentum

width outside off, and Tendulkar smashes off the back foot, looks to have picked the gap but Symonds does well to move across, dive and pick it up, underarm to Clarke on his left, who throws back to the stumps
finds the gap this time with some great driving, past cover, Hopes and Symonds combine inside the rope this time, Symonds hunting it down - just - flicking back, and Hopes does the rest
some swing outside off and then a swing from Uthappa, waited for that one, a slower one, and driven hard over mid-off and it rolled on its way
faster one this time at 147.7kph, swinging across him, and he goes for a lashing drive
oh, forces an intake of breath as he slides past the batsman who's on the back foot and just to say fails to take the edge
finds some lift first up, coming in on off, the batsman tucks down off the back foot
comes back in from outside off and defended on the back foot
a touch short this time on off, and tucked off the legs behind square to bring up the fifty partnership, eluding the diving fielder
back on the dime, defended down off the back foot this time
a change of length this time, Uthappa comes out, pokes at the ball with a firm stride outside off, and middes it, Gilchrist's keeping in a helmet by the way
oh hello, super catch, the ball firmly pulled off the legs to deep square, Hussey runs over, dives under and takes it low, immediately gets up and celebrates, arm up and a big yell of "Yes!"
jumps into the line and defends back into the crease outside off
defended back down once more
on off this time, pokes down and they take a suicidal run but Clarke can't kill him off with a shy on the dive from gully
good swing up to the batsman, on a good length too, but Gambhir manages to get the inside edge
drags it down short on the legs but gets away with it as Tendulkar tucks it off the hips to square
tucked him up on off, the batsman dropping the ball down dead and they run through quickly, better running than earlier in the over
pushed on to the back foot, plays down to third man
bustles the ball up there on off and played down  into the crease, Clarke spints up from gully and his underarm isn't quite on the money though the batsman was probably home
pushed into the covers

outside off, cut behind deep point and Tendulkar wants them to come back for two, but Gambhir is napping a touch, the throw comes back in from Johnson and Hopes collects the ball and shies on from a metre or so out
up there on off, and defended into the ground
outside off, plenty of width, and he drives hard, square on the off-side
tight ball, pushed on the front foot forward
swung up to the left hander who crunches out on the front foot to mid-on
tight up there in line with off, defended on the front foot
driven forward into the covers
rolls the ball down on to leg, the batsman pushes out to midwicket and Lee throws it in, nearly taking out Umpire Harper and the throw gets naughty cheers from the crowd
shortish ball on off, tuck-jumped out towards mid-on
short ball with some width outside off, cut down off the back foot to third man
pushed across the right hander, who drives on the tiptoes up to the covers
forced across the left hander from over the wicket, drives out to the covers
slower ball, good one, up there on middle, defended back on the front foot
forced across the left hander again who defends back down the pitch once more
outside off, lets that one go past him and it dies a touch as it does so
pushed across the right hander who drives smoothly out to mid-off on the front foot
outside off, cut down to third man
pushed very wide across him down off
on the legs, turned out to short midwicket
outside off, a touch of width, the ball is puhed out to mid-off where Hogg collects and gives the biggest hint-hint he wants to bowl by bowling the ball back to Johnson
tucked very well indeed off the legs, too straight for Johnson and it runs off way behind square
better ball, on off, full delivery, and defended forward
moves it back in to the right hander from just outside off, the batsman rocking back on to his back foot to drive back out to the covers
wide down leg, and Tendulkar chased it round, Gilchrist appealed for the strangle, nowhere near, though
on leg, Tendulkar pushes easily round the corner
extra loop on middle and leg, pushed up there and driven out
big loop again, Tendulkar moves back to make space and goes for the big drive over cover and it goes on its merry way, Yuvraj clapping his bat to shot his appreciation
pitches on middle, some awkward loop, backs away and defends in the end
on the legs, turned fine round the corner and there's an easy two
big swing in on a full delivery which pitches on middle and off, defended out with a dig
outside off, overpitched and the batsman launches into what's a well-struck cover drive
overpitched on middle and leg, and worked out well off the pads to midwicket
outside off, edged out back down through the vacant slip area
driven out square on the off side this time
pushed into the covers on the front foot for a quick single
full delivery, dipping on off, driven out square to point
pushed out in front of short midwicket this time
on middle, just a touch short and Tendulkar peels off a very fine pull shot to bring up a well-crafted fifty from 56 balls with four fours
beat Yuvraj this time with one which pitches on off
bowled him! Beat him for pace and the ball goes through and knocks back the sticks, Yuvraj not getting into the line of the legbreak as he rocks back out leaving his stumps exposed
